			<ul class="story-list format-xs">
				<li>
					<article>
						<figure class="thumb is-photo">
							<div class="fig-graphic">
								<a href="http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2013/11/what-happens-when-other-countries-start-droning-98996.html?ml=m_ms"><img src="http://images.politico.com/global/2013/11/01/drones_illo_close_c_630x342.jpg" /></a></div>
						</figure>
						<div class="summary">
							<header>
								<p class="category"><a href="http://www.politico.com/p/magazine/tag/the-great-american-boom">The Great American BOOM</a></p>
								<h3>
									<a href="http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2013/11/what-happens-when-other-countries-start-droning-98996.html?ml=m_ms">What Happens When Other Countries Start Droning?</a></h3>
							</header>
							<div class="meta">
								<p class="byline">By MICAH ZENKO</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</article>
				</li>
				<li>
					<article>
						<figure class="thumb is-photo">
							<div class="fig-graphic">
								<a href="http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2013/11/real-gamechangers-99377.html?ml=m_ms"><img src="http://images.politico.com/global/2013/11/07/real-gamechangers2_630x342.jpg" /></a></div>
						</figure>
						<div class="summary">
							<header>
								<p class="category"><a href="http://www.politico.com/p/magazine/tag/the-great-american-boom">The Great American BOOM</a></p>
								<h3>
									<a href="http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2013/11/real-gamechangers-99377.html?ml=m_ms">Real Game-Changers</a></h3>
							</header>
						</div>
					</article>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</aside>
</div>
<p>Our future will bring more wealthy people than ever before, but also more poor people, including people who do not always have access to basic public services. Rather than balancing our national budget with higher taxes or lower benefits, we will allow GDP growth to falter and the real wages of many workers to fall, creating a new underclass. But this polarization notwithstanding, America&rsquo;s political collapse is much less likely than the pessimists imagine, between the general aging of American society and the way new technologies are improving basic living standards.</p> <p>One day soon we will look back and see that we produced two radically different countries: a fantastically successful nation, working in the technologically dynamic sectors, and everyone else. It may not be precisely the dystopian future for our dying democracy that Isaac Asimov envisioned. But it won&rsquo;t be too far off, either.</p> <p><em>Tyler Cowen</em><em>&nbsp;is professor of economics at <a href="http://www.gmu.edu/centers/publicchoice/faculty%20pages/Tyler/" target="_blank">George Mason University</a>.</em> <em>This article was adapted from his book </em><a href="http://www.amazon.com/Average-Is-Over-Powering-Stagnation/dp/0525953736" target="_blank">Average Is Over: Powering America Beyond the Age of the Great Stagnation</a><em>, copyright &copy; 2013, and was published by arrangement with Dutton, which is a member of Penguin Group (USA) LLC, a Penguin Random House Company.</em></p>

						</div>
					
					
		<nav class="story-nav">
			

			<div class="pagination">
				<h6>Page:</h6>
				<ol>
					
					
						<li><a href="http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2013/11/the-robots-are-here-98995.html" rel="next"><span>&laquo;</span></a></li>
					<li ><a href="http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2013/11/the-robots-are-here-98995.html">1</a></li><li class="current"><a href="http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2013/11/the-robots-are-here-98995_Page2.html">2</a></li> 
				</ol>
			</div>
		</nav>
		
				</div>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
	
	
	
